comment: 1.050 OG, pitched at 60 degrres, hopefully that isn't too low, this yeast says it doesn't ferment well below 62 (unless active ferm), I figure when it start up it will go well above 62
didn't use the zest in the boil, may put in secondary?
finished at 1.010, low for this yeast, and it fermented cool, surprising. pitched at 60 and it got up to 65 during active, two weeks later its at 1.010
made a potion with 1 oz of mixed zest and 8 oz of vod, will add to keg to taste
